news.title: Government approves town planning schemes for Ahmedabad, Surat, Bhavnagar metropolis
news.para: The Seven town planning schemes which has been approved four preliminary TP schemes for Surat and one each preliminary TP schemes for Ahmedabad and Bhavnagar also includes one draft TP for Bavla.

news.title: Adani Properties raises Rs 800 crore from Credit Suisse
news.para: APPL, which raises finances for Adani Group companies, borrowed Rs 2,525 crore this fiscal year starting April at an average rate of 15% per annum and tenure of one to three years. All the funds were raised through zero-coupon bonds by pledging shares of SB Adani Family Trust, which holds the promoter shares of listed Adani Group companies, the people said.

news.title: Keppel Land to buy 1 million sq ft in Piramal Realty's office project for Rs 1,200 crore
news.para: Keppel Land has already signed the term sheet to acquire nearly 1 million sq ft of commercial real estate spread across a total six entire floors in this multi-tenanted tower. The transaction will exclude nearly 2 lakh sq ft office space occupied by Piramal enterprises.

news.title: Bengaluru development body vows to finish works at its layouts, but sets no deadline
news.para: The plan is to ready Anjanapura, Visvesvaraya and Banashankari 6 Stage (1, 2 blocks) layouts after completing pending civic works worth over Rs 400 crore.

news.title: Issues regarding NOC of sale-purchase of property to be solved soon: Punjab minister
news.para: The minister said that Punjab Government was now working on war footing in a transparent manner to address problems of the people in this regard.

news.title: Chandigarh: 26,000 property owners set to get revised tax bills
news.para: A majority of the revised property tax bills has been published. Sources said the distribution process will start in a day or two to cover all taxpayers falling under the category.

news.title: Deemed conveyance for 325 societies in Pune in 90 days
news.para: Of the 1,170 new cooperative housing societies, the maximum is from Thane (425), followed by Pune (325 in city and 50 in rural belt) and Mumbai (180).

news.title: Illegal additions to houses rampant but no crackdown: Noida RWAs
news.para: "It is the most common problem existing in every society. The RWA or the AOA has a very limited role. It tries to enforce norms but hardly gets success. In such a scenario, it is Noida Authority’s responsibility to enforce rules," said Rajiva Singh, president of NOFAA.

news.title: Ajmera Realty & Infra India's sales up 261% year-on-year in April-June
news.para: During the quarter, the company managed to reduce its debt by Rs 25 crore supported by sales and collection momentum. The developer’s weighted average cost of debt stood at 11.6% as on June end with debt-to-equity ratio at 1.12:1 as compared to 1.17:1 in the previous quarter.

news.title: Over 400 insolvency cases in real estate sector were going on as of June 2022: Government
news.para: In last financial year, 210 applications pertaining to real estate sector were admitted for CIRP under the Code. Out of them, 18 cases have been resolved, 60 have been settled or withdrawn and in 63 cases, liquidation has been ordered.

news.title: FIR likely against Sabyasachi Infrastructure for developing colony on agricultural land
news.para: In fact, the department had issued the showcause notice after its enforcement wing carried out an investigation and found that Sabyasachi Infrastructure developing a residential licensed plotted colony under the Deen Dayal Jan Aawas Yojna in Sector 3 of Farrukhnagar.

news.title: Circle rate hike deferred in Ghaziabad over objections
news.para: This is despite a proposal to hike the circle rates after a gap of six years. The district magistrate has attributed the delay to the rising number of objections and suggestions.

news.title: HDFC hikes lending rate by 25 basis points
news.para: ​The move came after RBI on Friday raised the benchmark lending rate by 50 basis points to 5.40 per cent in its effort to cool down rising inflation. Following the rate hike, borrowing from the central bank has become costlier.

news.title: Concreting with unapproved design mix led to poor construction quality of NBCC Green View
news.para: The minister said that as interim relief to the owners residing in Green View Apartments at 37 D Gurugram, an advance rental for six months has been provided along with shifting charges of household goods by NBCC.

news.title: SC grants interim bail to jailed Amrapali group CMD medical grounds
news.para: At the outset, Additional Solicitor General Aishwarya Bhati, appearing for Centre, said as per the advice of doctors, he does not require admission in hospital but he is in need of medical care.
